            <fr:title text="Least-Upper-Bound Property">Least-Upper-Bound Property</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/baby-rudin/" title="Principles of Mathematical Analysis" uri="http://localhost:8000/baby-rudin/" display-uri="baby-rudin" type="local">Principles of Mathematical Analysis</fr:link>, 1.10</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>An <fr:link href="/ca-0003/" title="Ordered Set" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-0003/" display-uri="ca-0003" type="local">Ordered Set</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is said to have the <html:dfn>Least-Upper-Bound Property</html:dfn> if the following is true:</html:p>
            <html:p>For any subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\subseteq  S]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is non empty and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/ca-0003/" title="Ordered Set" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-0003/" display-uri="ca-0003" type="local">bounded above</fr:link>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sup (E)]]></fr:tex> exists in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/alex-nelson/" title="Alex Nelson" uri="http://localhost:8000/alex-nelson/" display-uri="alex-nelson" type="local">Alex Nelson</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
