            <fr:title text="Upper bound, bounded above">Upper bound, bounded above</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/baby-rudin/" title="Principles of Mathematical Analysis" uri="http://localhost:8000/baby-rudin/" display-uri="baby-rudin" type="local">Principles of Mathematical Analysis</fr:link>, 1.7</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/ca-0003/" title="Ordered Set" uri="http://localhost:8000/ca-0003/" display-uri="ca-0003" type="local">Ordered Set</fr:link>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E\subseteq  S]]></fr:tex>. If there exists a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta \in  S]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\leq \beta ]]></fr:tex> for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  E]]></fr:tex>, then we say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Bounded Above</html:dfn> and call <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta ]]></fr:tex> an <html:dfn>Upper Bound</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Lower bounds are defined similarly: a <html:dfn>Lower Bound</html:dfn> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \in  S]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \leq  x]]></fr:tex> for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  E]]></fr:tex>, and we say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Bounded Below</html:dfn>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
